name: George Orwell
content: Big Brother is watching you.

name: Jane Austen
content: It is a truth universally acknowledged that a single man in possession of a good fortune must be in want of a wife.

name: Charles Dickens
content: It was the best of times it was the worst of times.

name: Mark Twain
content: The only way to do great work is to love what you do.

name: J.K. Rowling
content: It does not do to dwell on dreams and forget to live.

name: Ernest Hemingway
content: There is no friend as loyal as a book.

name: Leo Tolstoy
content: All happy families are alike each unhappy family is unhappy in its own way.

name: Harper Lee
content: You never really understand a person until you consider things from his point of view.

name: F. Scott Fitzgerald
content: So we beat on boats against the current borne back ceaselessly into the past.

name: Agatha Christie
content: The impossible could not have happened therefore the impossible must be possible in spite of appearances.

name: William Faulkner
content: The past is never dead. It's not even past.

name: Emily Bronte
content: Whatever our souls are made of his and mine are the same.

name: J.R.R. Tolkien
content: Not all those who wander are lost.

name: George R.R. Martin
content: Winter is coming.

name: Markus Zusak
content: I am haunted by humans.

name: Virginia Woolf
content: Lock up your libraries if you like but there is no gate no lock no bolt that you can set upon the freedom of my mind.

name: Albert Camus
content: In the depth of winter I finally learned that there was in me an invincible summer.

name: Louisa May Alcott
content: Life is my college. May I graduate well and earn some honors!

name: Oscar Wilde
content: To live is the rarest thing in the world. Most people exist that is all.

name: Robert Frost
content: Two roads diverged in a wood and I took the one less traveled by And that has made all the difference.

name: Charlotte Bronte
content: I am no bird and no net ensnares me: I am a free human being with an independent will.

name: Ernest Hemingway
content: There is no hunting like the hunting of man and those who have hunted armed men long enough and liked it never care for anything else thereafter.

name: Herman Melville
content: Call me Ishmael.

name: John Steinbeck
content: I've done a lot of living in my time but the saddest thing I've ever seen is a human being with a closed mind.

name: Victor Hugo
content: Even the darkest night will end and the sun will rise.

name: Maya Angelou
content: You may not control all the events that happen to you but you can decide not to be reduced by them.

name: Leo Tolstoy
content: If you look for perfection you'll never be content.

name: Haruki Murakami
content: Pain is inevitable. Suffering is optional.

name: George Orwell
content: War is peace. Freedom is slavery. Ignorance is strength.

name: Albert Einstein
content: Imagination is more important than knowledge. For knowledge is limited whereas imagination embraces the entire world stimulating progress giving birth to evolution.
